  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/1262156/" class="title-link">言说和倾听</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-1262156"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/roada9m/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img1.doubanio.com/icon/user_normal.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/roada9m/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">[已注销]</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2007-12-18"
      class="main-meta">2007-12-18 12:28:17</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_1262156_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  言说。  思与诗，海德格尔属于思。他谈论诗，热爱诗人，自己也写诗，但海德格尔不是荷尔德林。在《艺术作品的本源》中，他说：“一切艺术本质上皆是诗”。 由于对诗的热爱，思者又如是说：诗本质上也是思。然而思毕竟不同于诗。  什么是诗？“筹划着的道说就是诗。” 诗是道说...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/1262156/#comments">(12回应)</a>
